transcription.text:
Speaker 1: Thank you for calling Viagra, how can I help you?

Speaker 2: Yes, my name is Sterling Garns, and I had placed an order online. It was a one-time deal. And I received my order, and you sent me something else today.

Speaker 1: Let me help you out.

Speaker 2: I don't need it.

Speaker 1: All right, can you just confirm your date of birth?

Speaker 2: 11-29-48.

Speaker 1: Thank you so much. I see you're a VIP status customer.

Speaker 2: Oh, I see the doctor put you on refills on a monthly basis,

Speaker 1: which you do not have to have.

Speaker 2: How's the medication working out for you?

Speaker 1: Oh, I have no complaints.

Speaker 2: OK, yeah, so with your VIP status,

Speaker 1: you don't have to have your refills on a monthly basis.

Speaker 2: What a lot of people like to do is just

Speaker 1: go ahead and pause their refills for up to six months.

Speaker 2: That way, it keeps your prescription active

Speaker 1: and keeps you locked in at your price point.

Speaker 2: So if rates do go up, yours will stay the same.

Speaker 1: And it just allows you to call in whenever you need a refill.

Speaker 2: I could pause that for you until July 31st.

Speaker 1: And then if you don't need a refill,

Speaker 2: then you just call and pause it further.

Speaker 1: That way, you keep your price.

Speaker 2: No, I think I'll just let it go.

Speaker 1: I'll let it go.

Speaker 2: All right, not a problem.

Speaker 1: All right, you're all canceled out.

Speaker 2: You're all set.

Speaker 1: OK, I appreciate it.

Speaker 2: Thank you very much.

Speaker 1: No problem.

Speaker 2: Have a good day.

Speaker 1: You too.

Speaker 2: Thanks, bye.
